abstract: Some members of the special counsel’s team say the attorney general failed to adequately portray their findings.

lead_paragraph: Good Thursday morning. Here are some of the stories making news in Washington and politics today.
headline_main: On Politics: Investigators for Mueller Say Barr Underplayed Report

abstract: The logic seems to go that everyone is better off, even minorities, when white people are calling the shots.
snippet: The logic seems to go that everyone is better off, even minorities, when white people are calling the shots.
lead_paragraph: Donald Trump’s lie-filled rage tweets about Puerto Rico this week over disaster aid continue a Trump pattern that mirrors a method that white supremacists have used throughout American history. Particularly present since Reconstruction, this method involves proclaiming that minorities lack the character and capacity to create effective government, and therefore minority-led jurisdictions are a hopeless drain on resources.

abstract: The fund-raising total is smaller than what Senators Bernie Sanders and Kamala Harris have revealed, but Mr. O’Rourke only joined the presidential race in mid-March.
snippet: The fund-raising total is smaller than what Senators Bernie Sanders and Kamala Harris have revealed, but Mr. O’Rourke only joined the presidential race in mid-March.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Former Representative Beto O’Rourke of Texas raised $9.4 million over the first 18 days of his presidential bid, his campaign said on Wednesday, the latest sign of his ability to attract online donors even within a packed Democratic field.

abstract: The announcement puts Mr. Sanders ahead of the other Democratic presidential candidates who have announced their first-quarter fund-raising numbers.
snippet: The announcement puts Mr. Sanders ahead of the other Democratic presidential candidates who have announced their first-quarter fund-raising numbers.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont raised $18.2 million over the first six weeks of his presidential bid, his campaign announced Tuesday, a display of financial strength that cements his status as one of the top fund-raisers in the sprawling Democratic field.

abstract: It’s not whether to run, but whether to run against the emerging consensus of his party.
snippet: It’s not whether to run, but whether to run against the emerging consensus of his party.
lead_paragraph: At some point soon, Joe Biden is going to have to make two decisions. The first is whether he wants to run for the Democratic nomination. The second is whether he wants to win it, and at what cost.

abstract: The California senator received 218,000 contributions, and 98 percent were under $100.
snippet: The California senator received 218,000 contributions, and 98 percent were under $100.
lead_paragraph: Senator Kamala Harris announced Monday night that her 2020 campaign raised $12 million in her first two-plus months running for president, a sum that is expected to vault her into the top tier of financial competitors in the wide-open Democratic primary.
